      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to take your Sertraline, but adding St. John's Wort is a dangerous mistake that could cause your serotonin levels to crash dangerously low. These two herbs are notorious for creating a \"herb-drug interaction\" that can lead to severe depression, suicidal thoughts, and even life-threatening withdrawal symptoms. St. John's Wort is so potent that it can easily override the calming effects of your antidepressant, leaving you feeling worse than before. I strongly advise against mixing them; instead, focus on rest, hydration, and perhaps a small snack to stabilize your energy. Please stop taking the herb immediately and contact your doctor right away to discuss your symptoms safely.",
