      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, that is not a mild case; it is a life-threatening interaction that can cause your brain to shut down completely. St. John's Wort contains compounds that directly inhibit the enzymes your Sertraline needs to break down, leading to a sudden and severe drop in serotonin levels that can trigger severe depression or suicidal ideation. It is not safe to mix them, even for \"mild\" cases, because the risk of a dangerous crash is too high. Please stop taking the herb immediately and contact your doctor right away to discuss your symptoms safely.",
